uded and how the resource metadata comes into play. It's interesting to think that the agent is supposed to detect these details. There's a lot to unpack here!\n\n**Considering class modifications**\n\nIt looks like I have a class that isn’t public, which violates the rule that all top-level test classes must be public. Right now, it has a placeholder that's package-private. If I want to modify it, I’ll need to either fix it or remove it. I could replace the file with a dedicated test, but the mapping indicates it's for SecuritySupportTest. Should I delete XmlParserAPIsTest using bash rm instead? And, maybe I don't need AssertJ—I'll just go with JUnit assertions.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8cf4c82448190895600f022cf1133\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-M9klE72SFAZMD_6JXORK0w_UnqCTuxcA_QTRaPJpCHhF8vM_niqYgXqt7vnEsKe9uA3uP2wcV29SN7AhB_X0itiMyuSbxYU4TpRkxxJ4yNLSeED2JL8CEd51sgQBcS6wRYwXALqYo2ZlbJcb0BjqSLf-BRdcTJw9HHQ1XWmw2d1dMw5uBO9Syh_OlMR0rU4U02Kai3TkIJNsO9ZT7mEw0bSRk7IaiSdmRpBnI586W6CdKSNAAi32ay8NF_GvVidArFDPYZfYtNfiY5exfcC6ir-ywMpGxVTUO4Xe76yLYtyXiqrj7NuN1FGFkcOLY3vgAoQ7OiUoVGgagrrQ9F7spToIOG3DqIcdVdr3P8QiYAxEmO5DLCXxNBfHHNr3fcyOom3QM-a9oB4zrD949wHHST_AzmXQHljzxWRy7SuiMxbh_-UB2r9HnqIyrF06y28nMSwrdlVPrECPvKEyZD5ubPEvqS_7XEnHwhVxOuep3nXkeimCks7BdAK9Zxq01q2K1UMXbbl_7LScG-2qNu03Z0oEw8B5aX_OgqG3ai3o86JoimTeIPrZA-cVdYhyQNuBrBNANzMwS7qZk14lYT6UxaAHn0Fs1OGS2EHt-NzT2tHKVOgR0vDqlf0eGLozgdnWNbI_C7y2LwsFH5Gu00PO6RQ8sK__UWtmmrYDO9BcPGBKTXuM10wMNGGkogSvlUebeAcpKZtA8UfRcQQ6Lq1IZzKfAu2RmFM9kTGj9G4og8KJAtncTWq3EvOhExkhv7Yh0g7NfGCNxjK1-B2b7tG1FT1Khrx9_49rhUw0WzQnzAMEX7lcgMXiIj-LeEuTyYuJkzzcsQBp7rxgdFuyUPF3gkoktGFKgd_jR30ZRv_Kf-6qEDiWesrTObcCMgcTCenrxlU5WRBaijZXcg1kkHAmcGMuozv24Heuq344I3Wa5z7dqIYYA60SWT2gsJYJuYx9d-71q2SRgIT6TaKH1Aqddp3vxdzBKysJqLce7qUs4SHq9Wo9bmx054VfKuwog6Dg-gWC6KH7KWwn-qH7Ycip2cO_9hJlVhoRbl3BoGbfDeAyb4DzcjuSE2GAFqtOw9NXMO8ewjHAjw43AFiHQBqlQzfbh1EqYUdf68Wm7BhvDD7eyWv7J1jd4D2hnQBeXNYaLFtlUywK64QHJ3o-_ZyW7AEQC79ZsN