t to unravel!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Understanding custom classloader behavior**\\n\\nI'm considering what happens if a custom classloader hides SecuritySupport12. It looks like a NoClassDefFoundError would occur since that's an error and not an exception, leading to static initialization failure. If the custom classloader denies access to java.security.AccessController, Class.forName may throw a ClassNotFoundException. Custom loaders may need to override loadClass, and I’m curious whether the parent classloader could still define it. I need to think this through to get a clearer understanding!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Gradle tests**\\n\\nI'm looking into how resources are handled in Gradle tests. Should they be on the system classloader? Or is modern JUnit relying on the app classloader? When it comes to native images, I wonder if resources need to be included and how the resource metadata comes into play. It's interesting to think that the agent is supposed to detect these details. There's a lot to unpack here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class modifications**\\n\\nIt looks like I have a class that isn’t public, which violates the rule that all top-level test classes must be public. Right now, it has a placeholder that's package-private. If I want to modify it, I’ll need to either fix it or remove it. I could replace the file with a dedicated test, but the mapping indicates it's for SecuritySupportTest. Should I delete XmlParserAPIsTest using bash rm instead? And, maybe I don't need AssertJ—I'll just go with JUnit assertions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gAaXRfVyoKTyue5TmMhTFmL4|fc_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8cf6418088190941f6b9eb3637ef6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rm tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/XmlParserAPIsTest.java && mkdir -p tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/resources/xerces/xmlParserAPIs"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 730, "output": 1597, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30487, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777913675276, "responseId": "resp_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8cf4bbf58819098617e65c04d3385"}}
