t's good. There's possibly an issue with `URLClassLoader` not being able to load specific packages. I also need to think about import order and existing Checkstyle rules around imports regarding blank spaces. Finally, `InvocationTargetException` handling could be tricky with dynamic class loading.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring URLClassLoader issues**\\n\\nIt looks like there are compatibility issues with `URLClassLoader`, making it unable to handle some tests, especially when using method reflection like `Method.invoke`. If `ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream` throws an error in native, it wraps it in an `InvocationTargetException`, causing test failures. I'm wondering if the problem lies in the classpath used by the Gradle JUnit worker, which may not include certain libraries due to the manifest jar. Using `Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()` to access resources could be a more robust solution.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing parent-first class loader behavior**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the parent-first class loader can still find resources in the jar, even if the class itself didn’t load due to the split issue. It seems like resources could potentially still be visible. If the resource URL points to something like `jar:file:...!/javax/xml...`, then parsing that jar file could provide access to the needed resources. So, exploring this route might be worthwhile to ensure I’m covering all bases!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_26UPSSTIjMzrTIU5xJt5aHgj|fc_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8d01476b8819089af8124f05c0cc0", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/SecuritySupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n", "newText": "import java.net.JarURLConnection;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static File findXmlParserApisJar(ClassNotFoundException originalException) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        String classPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\", \"\");\n        for (String entry : classPath.split(File.pathSeparator)) {\n            File file = new File(entry);\n            if (file.getName().startsWith(\"xmlParserAPIs-\") && file.getName().endsWith(\".jar\")) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n        throw originalException;\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static File findXmlParserApisJar(ClassNotFoundException originalException) throws Exception {\n        String classPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\", \"\");\n        for (String entry : classPath.split(File.pathSeparator)) {\n            File file = new File(entry);\n            if (isXmlParserApisJar(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        ClassLoader classLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        Enumeration<URL> resources = classLoader.getResources(\"javax/xml/parsers/SecuritySupport.class\");\n        while (resources.hasMoreElements()) {\n            URL resource = resources.nextElement();\n            if (\"jar\".equals(resource.getProtocol())) {\n                JarURLConnection connection = (JarURLConnection) resource.openConnection();\n                File file = new File(connection.getJarFileURL().toURI());\n                if (isXmlParserApisJar(file)) {\n                    return file;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        throw originalException;\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isXmlParserApisJar(File file) {\n        return file.getName().startsWith(\"xmlParserAPIs-\") && file.getName().endsWith(\".jar\");\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2145, "output": 1188, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45829, "c