quGYFAzSC06_B3-2kY_20Wfbb-XOhLA2A0eE_TGmT8op-kl6yfUDDGUr0fE1KqQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI’m considering how to modify the code to handle native path dynamic class loading effectively. It seems that if it’s unsupported, I should yield an error message by trying URLClassLoader directly. I don’t think skipping this step is an option. I wonder if the native image support for URLClassLoader might throw an error at the constructor level. It seems important to investigate this further to ensure smooth functionality.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering resource visibility in JVM**\\n\\nI'm contemplating resource visibility within modules. In the JVM, classpath resources can involve split packages, and it seems like getResources could find resources in jars. In a native context, resources may be unavailable unless properly configured. I think ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream might not work well for class resources. There's a possibility of encountering a CNFE if dynamic loading fails. I’m thinking it could be simpler to use URLClassLoader instead.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Qli0VLTOSwh0X2abNKQK31C4|fc_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8d11427cc819099cd51af6825717c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsSupport.java tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/SecuritySupportTest.java | sed -n '1,260p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 920, "output": 1654, "cacheRead": 64000, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 66574, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777914106552, "responseId": "resp_03505b97eae3fcb30169f8d0fb411881909ebc67804749195d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Qli0VLTOSwh0X2abNKQK31C4|fc_03505b